# Write Descriptive Atomic Commits

Write atomic commits for each task you complete that read like an ingishtful changelog.

Examples:

```bash
git add -A && git commit -m "core: decouple theme chain/assets resolution from TemplateEngine via utils.theme_resolution; use in Site"
git add -A && git commit -m "core(server): add Site.reset_ephemeral_state and adopt in dev server; utils: introduce ProgressReporter; orchestration: route streaming output via reporter" --no-verify
git add -A && git commit -m "docs(plan): add decoupling roadmap draft with phased actions and value rationale"
git add -A && git commit -m "orchestration: avoid mutating site.pages during render; pass explicit page list"
```
